From 38f058162d7e1b9b838b5f7c036bf5ccf756fa42 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 18:15:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] feat: async jobs over Redis Streams, single-writer index
 with WAL and versioned snapshots

Fase 3 of the plain-text manager plan:
- Job aggregate with enforced PENDING->RUNNING->DONE/FAILED transitions;
  JobService submits/executes index, search and delete jobs (failures
  recorded as FAILED state, never lost)
- mode=async on POST /index and /search returns 202 {job_id}; new
  GET /jobs/{id} polling endpoint, tenant-scoped (RF-13)
- job backends: inline in-process default (same API contract), Redis
  string state + Streams transport with consumer groups; abandoned
  pending messages reclaimed via XAUTOCLAIM (at-least-once, idempotent
  execution by content-hash dedup + deterministic chunk ids)
- indexer worker (python -m app.workers.indexer_worker): the single
  writer; VersionedIndexWriter adds fsync'd JSONL WAL, replay-on-start
  recovery, threshold checkpoints to immutable index.v{N} files, atomic
  manifest flips and old-version pruning (ADR-010, NFR-07)
- HotReloadingVectorIndex: read-only replica view that follows the
  manifest; worker_mode replicas force index/delete through jobs
- SearchService extracted so route and worker share one search path;
  composition root moved to app/bootstrap.py (web + worker wiring)
- 253 tests green

